Pattern of pedal glands (
Figure 6
). UpG cordiform and as wide as MeG, becoming L-shaped in middle chaetigers. LoG triangular or elliptical and shorter than UpG in anterior chaetigers, becoming shorter in middle chaetigers. MeG rounded and 3 times larger than PoG, subequal in middle chaetigers. PoG becoming larger towards middle chaetigers.
